1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on convolutional networks and their design for image processing tasks. 
2. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also likely as the paper discusses the impact of varying the number of layers and parameters on the performance of the network. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper deals with the design and optimization of deep learning architectures. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper deals with the design and optimization of deep learning models, which are a key component of AI systems. 
5. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the impact of varying the dimensionality of the representation in convolutional networks, which is relevant to natural language processing tasks.
